le=3D"Expected value">expected</a> number of successes remains fixed =E2=80=
=94 see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_distribution#law_o=
f_rare_events">law of rare events</a> below. Therefore, it can be used as a=
n approximation of the binomial distribution if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar=
" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> is sufficiently large and <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">p</span> is sufficiently s=
mall. The Poisson distribution is a good approximation of the binomial dist=
ribution if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</sp=
an> is at least&nbsp;20 and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-styl=
e:italic;">p</span> is smaller than or equal to&nbsp;0.05, and an excellent=
 approximation if <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=89=A5 100</span> and=
 <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>np</i> =E2=89=A4 10</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
NIST2006_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
