<p>Some applications of the Poisson distribution to <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Count_data" title=3D"Count data">count data</a> (number o=
f events):<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Rasch1963_57-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_distribution#cite_note-Rasch1963-=
57"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>57<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telecommunication" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Telecommunication">telecommunication</a>: telepho=
ne calls arriving in a system,</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy" title=3D"Astronomy"=
>astronomy</a>: photons arriving at a telescope,</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemistry" title=3D"Chemistry"=
>chemistry</a>: the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molar_mass_dis=
tribution" title=3D"Molar mass distribution">molar mass distribution</a> of=
 a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Living_polymerization" title=3D=
"Living polymerization">living polymerization</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Flory=
1940_58-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poi=
sson_distribution#cite_note-Flory1940-58"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>58<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biology" title=3D"Biology">bio=
logy</a>: the number of mutations on a strand of <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/DNA" title=3D"DNA">DNA</a> per unit length,</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management" title=3D"Managemen=
t">management</a>: customers arriving at a counter or call centre,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-59" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Poisson_distribution#cite_note-59"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
59<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finance_and_insurance" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Finance and insurance">finance and insurance</a>:=
 number of losses or claims occurring in a given period of time,</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earthquake_seismology" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Earthquake seismology">seismology</a>: asymptotic=
 Poisson model of risk for large earthquakes,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Lomnitz199=
4_60-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisso=
n_distribution#cite_note-Lomnitz1994-60"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>60<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radioactivity" class=3D"mw-red=
irect" title=3D"Radioactivity">radioactivity</a>: decays in a given time in=
terval in a radioactive sample,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-61" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_distribution#cite_note-61"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>61<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Optics" title=3D"Optics">optic=
s</a>: number of photons emitted in a single laser pulse (a major vulnerabi=
lity of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_key_distribution" =
title=3D"Quantum key distribution">quantum key distribution</a> protocols, =
known as photon number splitting).</li></ul>
<p>More examples of counting events that may be modelled as Poisson process=
es include:
</p>
<ul><li>soldiers killed by horse-kicks each year in each corps in the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prussia" title=3D"Prussia">Prussian</a>=
