<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Poisson_regression_and_nega=
tive_binomial_regression">Poisson regression and negative binomial regressi=
on</h3></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_regression" title=3D"Po=
isson regression">Poisson regression</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Negative_binomial" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Negative binom=
ial">negative binomial</a> regression are useful for analyses where the dep=
endent (response) variable is the count <span class=3D"texhtml">(0, 1, 2, .=
.. )</span> of the number of events or occurrences in an interval.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Biology">Biology</h3></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luria%E2%80%93Delbr%C3%BCck=
_experiment" title=3D"Luria=E2=80=93Delbr=C3=BCck experiment">Luria=E2=80=
=93Delbr=C3=BCck experiment</a> tested against the hypothesis of Lamarckian=
 evolution, which should result in a Poisson distribution.=20
</p><p>Katz and Miledi measured the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Membrane_potential" title=3D"Membrane potential">membrane potential</a> w=
ith and without the presence of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ac=
etylcholine" title=3D"Acetylcholine">acetylcholine</a> (ACh).<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-74" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pois=
son_distribution#cite_note-74"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>74<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> When ACh is present, <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ion_channel" title=3D"Ion channel">ion channe=
ls</a> on the membrane would be open randomly at a small fraction of the ti=
me. As there are a large number of ion channels each open for a small fract=
ion of the time, the total number of ion channels open at any moment is Poi=
sson distributed. When ACh is not present, effectively no ion channels are =
open. The membrane potential is <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-el=
ement-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" s=
tyle=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" =
alttext=3D"{\displaystyle V=3DN_{\text{open}}V_{\text{ion}}+V_{0}+V_{\text{=
