<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Random_variate_generation">=
Random variate generation</h3></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Further information: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-uniform_r=
andom_variate_generation" title=3D"Non-uniform random variate generation">N=
on-uniform random variate generation</a></div>
<p>The less trivial task is to draw integer <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Random_variate" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Random variate">ra=
ndom variate</a> from the Poisson distribution with given <span class=3D"mw=
e-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inli=
ne mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www=
.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \lambda .}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>=CE=BB<!-- =CE=BB --></mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lambda .}</a=
nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/4bb9c58e3f6b2de892e10ef516f96f07da0423e0" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:2.002ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \la=
mbda .}"></span>
</p><p>Solutions are provided by:
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R_(programming_language)" =
title=3D"R (programming language)">R</a>: function <code>rpois(n, lambda)</=
code>;</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU_Scientific_Library" title=
=3D"GNU Scientific Library">GNU Scientific Library</a> (GSL): function <a r=
el=3D"nofollow" class=3D"external text" href=3D"https://www.gnu.org/softwar=
e/gsl/doc/html/randist.html#the-poisson-distribution">gsl_ran_poisson</a></=
li></ul>
<p>A simple algorithm to generate random Poisson-distributed numbers (<a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudo-random_number_sampling" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Pseudo-random number sampling">pseudo-random number =
sampling</a>) has been given by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Do=
nald_Knuth" title=3D"Donald Knuth">Knuth</a>:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Knuth1997_=
79-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_=
distribution#cite_note-Knuth1997-79"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7=
9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference now=
rap"><span title=3D"Page: 137-138">:=E2=80=8A137-138=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
<pre><b>algorithm</b> <i>poisson random number (Knuth)</i>:
    <b>init</b>:
        <b>Let</b> L =E2=86=90 <i>e</i><sup>=E2=88=92<i>=CE=BB</i></sup>, k=
 =E2=86=90 0 and p =E2=86=90 1.
    <b>do</b>:
        k =E2=86=90 k + 1.
        Generate uniform random number u in [0,1] and <b>let</b> p =E2=86=
=90 p =C3=97 u.
    <b>while</b> p &gt; L.
    <b>return</b> k =E2=88=92 1.
</pre>
<p>The complexity is linear in the returned value <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">k</span>, which is <span class=3D"texhtml =
mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=BB</span> on average.  There are man=
y other algorithms to improve this. Some are given in Ahrens &amp; Dieter, =
see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_distribution#Reference=
s">=C2=A7&nbsp;References</a> below.
</p><p>For large values of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">=CE=BB</span>, the value of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>L</i> =3D =
<i>e</i><sup>=E2=88=92<i>=CE=BB</i></sup></span> may be so small that it is=
 hard to represent.  This can be solved by a change to the algorithm which =
uses an additional parameter STEP such that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>e</i=
><sup>=E2=88=92STEP</sup></span> does not underflow: <sup class=3D"noprint =
Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedi=
a:Citation needed"><span title=3D"Original source is missing (March 2019)">=
citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p>
<pre><b>algorithm</b> <i>poisson random number (Junhao, based on Knuth)</i>=
:
    <b>init</b>:
        <b>Let</b> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;=
">=CE=BB</span>Left =E2=86=90 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-st=
yle:italic;">=CE=BB</span>, k =E2=86=90 0 and p =E2=86=90 1.
    <b>do</b>:
        k =E2=86=90 k + 1.
        Generate uniform random number u in (0,1) and <b>let</b> p =E2=86=
=90 p =C3=97 u.
        <b>while</b> p &lt; 1 and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fon=
t-style:italic;">=CE=BB</span>Left &gt; 0:
            <b>if</b> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">=CE=BB</span>Left &gt; STEP:
                p =E2=86=90 p =C3=97 <i>e</i><sup>STEP</sup>
                <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=
=CE=BB</span>Left =E2=86=90 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-styl=
e:italic;">=CE=BB</span>Left =E2=88=92 STEP
            <b>else</b>:
                p =E2=86=90 p =C3=97 <i>e</i><sup><span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=BB</span>Left</sup>
                <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=
=CE=BB</span>Left =E2=86=90 0
    <b>while</b> p &gt; 1.
    <b>return</b> k =E2=88=92 1.
</pre>
<p>The choice of STEP depends on the threshold of overflow. For double prec=
ision floating point format the threshold is near <span class=3D"texhtml"><=
i>e</i><sup>700</sup></span>, so&nbsp;500 should be a safe <span class=3D"t=
exhtml"><i>STEP</i></span>.
</p><p>Other solutions for large values of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" sty=
le=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=BB</span> include <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Rejection_sampling" title=3D"Rejection sampling">rejection sa=
mpling</a> and using Gaussian approximation.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_transform_sampling"=
 title=3D"Inverse transform sampling">Inverse transform sampling</a> is sim=
ple and efficient for small values of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D=
"font-style:italic;">=CE=BB</span>, and requires only one uniform random nu=
mber <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">u</span> per=
 sample. Cumulative probabilities are examined in turn until one exceeds <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">u</span>.
</p>
<pre><b>algorithm</b> <i>Poisson generator based upon the inversion by sequ=
ential search</i>:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Devroye1986_80-0" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poisson_distribution#cite_note-De=
vroye1986-80"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>80<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Pag=
e: 505">:=E2=80=8A505=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
    <b>init</b>:
        <b>Let</b> x =E2=86=90 0, p =E2=86=90 <i>e</i><sup>=E2=88=92<i>=CE=
=BB</i></sup>, s =E2=86=90 p.
        Generate uniform random number u in [0,1].
    <b>while</b> u &gt; s <b>do</b>:
        x =E2=86=90 x + 1.
        p =E2=86=90 p =C3=97 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-sty=
le:italic;">=CE=BB</span> / x.
        s =E2=86=90 s + p.
    <b>return</b> x.
</pre>
